column1:
Source: U.S. Census Bureau, 1990, 2000, and 2010 Censuses of Population (corrected), and 2017 County Total Population Estimates.

1) The FIPS codes uniquely identify each county and are part of the Federal Information Processing Series (FIPS) managed by the American National Standards Institute (ANSI). For more information, see the Census Bureau’s list of ANSI geographic codes.

2) The 2013 rural-urban continuum codes classify metropolitan counties (codes 1 through 3) by size of the Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA), and nonmetropolitan counties (codes 4 through 9) by degree of urbanization and proximity to metro areas. See rural-urban continuum codes for precise definitions of each code.
